Create a full production HTML template with accessibility best practices

Below is a **production‑style HTML template** for the AQARIONZ WebUI that follows modern accessibility best practices: semantic landmarks, ARIA roles, proper headings, keyboard navigation, and responsive design.[1][2][3]

You can use this as the base shell and plug your 3D canvas and JS into the `<main>` section.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <title>AQARIONZ System Console</title>
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />

  <!-- Basic meta -->
  <meta name="description" content="AQARIONZ multi-layer system console for matter, signals, brains, and governance." />
  <meta name="theme-color" content="#040509" />

  <!-- Accessibility-friendly base styles -->
  <style>
    :root {
      --bg: #040509;
      --bg-soft: #0b0d17;
      --accent: #4b8bff;
      --accent-soft: rgba(75,139,255,0.18);
      --border: rgba(255,255,255,0.18);
      --text: #f5f5ff;
      --muted: #a5a7c5;
      --danger: #ff4b8b;
      --success: #44d17a;
      --focus: #ffcc57;
    }

    *, *::before, *::after {
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    html {
      font-size: 16px;
    }

    body {
      margin: 0;
      min-height: 100vh;
      font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", sans-serif;
      background: radial-gradient(circle at top, #181a2a 0, #040509 40%, #000 100%);
      color: var(--text);
      -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
    }

    /* Skip link */
    .skip-link {
      position: absolute;
      left: -999px;
      top: 0;
      padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
      background: #000;
      color: #fff;
      z-index: 100;
    }
